-// Phase 6 (Patch 0010 rewrite): Inventory panel — lifetime petal counts.
+// Patch 0031: Inventory v4 — clean rewrite using understood mental model.
 //
-// Layout: a 6-column grid sorted by (rarity ASC, petal_id ASC). Empty cells
-// (count == 0) hide via per-cell should_render. Format counts with
-// format_score (5_000 → "5k", 5e6 → "5m").
+// I spent the previous 4 patches on this panel (0022, 0023, 0027, 0028) and
+// the last two regressed things. After reading Element / Container / Renderer
+// / ScrollContainer end to end I now know exactly what was wrong and why:
 //
-// Patch 0010 changes from v1:
-//   - True multi-col grid (was: row-per-rarity HContainer).
-//   - Drops `Game::should_render_title_ui()` gate — panel must stay open
-//     when the player enters the game. Lives in other_ui_window now.
+//   - 0027 drew the count badge BEFORE the sprite. The sprite's scaled
+//     translate frame extended into the top-right corner and painted over
+//     the badge text. User saw "counts disappeared".
+//   - 0028 used manual `scale(1/0.62)` to undo the sprite scale before
+//     drawing the name. Floating-point error left a dirty transform; the
+//     name/badge ended up at slightly wrong coords and the ScrollContainer
+//     clip probably cropped them. Whole panel looked like an empty box.
+//   - 0028 also nested an HContainer inside an HFlexContainer for the
+//     Wipe+title header. HFlex stretches its own width to parent, then
+//     applies h_justify shift to the nested HContainer, then the nested
+//     HContainer applies its own h_justify shift to wipe — both shifts
+//     compound LEFTWARD and push the wipe button OUT of the panel.
+//
+// v4 ironclad rules (don't break these):
+//
+//   1. Inside any nested transform, wrap it in a `RenderContext` so the
+//      matrix + canvas state auto-restores. Never use manual inverse-scale.
+//   2. Draw order for cells: bg → sprite → name → BADGE (badge is LAST so
+//      nothing paints over it).
+//   3. Header stays in the proven v3 layout: HFlex(title, close). Wipe
+//      lives as a separate row at the BOTTOM of the panel (footer), where
+//      it can't muck with the title alignment math.
+//   4. ScrollContainer max_height = 360. Total grid ~840px so the bar is
+//      ALWAYS active. No more "scrollbar disappeared" bug.
+//   5. Cell 60×80 with sprite top, name middle-bottom, badge top-right.
+//   6. petal_name rendered at 9pt with stroke 0.22 for readability over
+//      saturated rarity backgrounds.
 
